The Minister explained that the EU was committed to reducing its greenhouse gas emissions by 20 per cent by 2020 compared to the level reached in 1990, regardless of the success of the signing of the "After 2012 Agreement", and was ready to reduce them by 30 per cent if the other major regions of the world and/or developing countries were also prepared to make commitments appropriate to their responsibility and capacity.
