Celebrations are not uniform in the EU and the United States either.
Hungarian legislation distinguishes national and state holidays and rest days.
Rest days are often linked to religious festivals or important historical events.
In Hungary, we celebrate the new year, the last day of the year that ends and the first day of the new year are also rest days, especially so that awakeners can rest quietly.
In addition, in a year, we have in all eleven red parties.
March 15 is a national festival, commemorating the revolution of 1848, as on October 23 as well as the commemorative day of the revolution of 1956.
On August 20, we celebrate the constitution of our state, May 1 is the work party and November 1 and 2, we remember our family members and our dead friends.
In addition, we have two days at Easter, Pentecost and Christmas.
The days of our state, national or even religious holidays rarely fall on a weekend, according to the calendar, it has become common to reorganize working days in cases or only one working day before or after the party marked in red.
It is true that we pay the price of extended weekends by working or going to school on Saturday before the extended weekend.
For many years, the Minister of Labour has ruled in particular on days of replacement of days before or after parties.
The Act extends to all employers and their employees, civil servants and persons working in the public service.
It does not, however, apply to service companies, institutions that are constantly turning and in service, through their vocation, and also to rest days.
This year, working days will be changed only around the end-of-the-year holidays: from December 24, life stops almost throughout the country because according to experience most people do rather overtime or take vacations they have saved for these purposes to spend the days between Christmas and New Year's Day at home.
