Congress approves the transposition of the Mifid, which entered into force on 1 November.
In parallel with its parliamentary formality, which ended today with the vote of the Congress of amendments incorporated into the bill in the Senate, the Government has submitted to a public hearing the regulation that will develop the new law, with the objective of its entry into force before the end of the year.
The representatives of the various groups agreed to highlight the efforts made by MPs and senators to negotiate and agree on the best regulation to ensure investor protection and to regulate in detail the organization's activity to ensure that markets operate effectively.
Mifid, which amends the Securities Market Act, implies the modernisation of financial markets, as it strengthens investor protection, improves the powers of the leaders of the National Securities Market Commission (CNMV) and promotes cooperation among the various leaders of the European Union.
The new regulations will provide financial consultation services for both special social reasons and natural or legal persons and create a new type of financial services (ESIS), financial consulting companies (AFI), which merge value companies, securities agencies and portfolio managers.
In addition, it increases the number of operations systems on financial instruments so that it is possible to add multilateral trading systems and order internationalization systems to regulated secondary markets, which compete with current stock exchange managers.
The Act also requires investment service companies to disclose on the market information on key aspects of their business profile, risk exposure and risk management, and requires them to keep a record of all operations they perform, to facilitate control by the NCMV.
By passing through the Congressional Economic Commission, several amendments have been added, including one showing that the debt held will be considered as a "complex" financial instrument given its high risk to the investor, which has demonstrated itself with what happened with the debt of high-risk American mortgages (subprime).
In addition, they took advantage of the management's transposition to legally define the functions that graduates in the Economy may have 30 years after, in 1977, it was approved, the royal decree which demarcates the professional functions reserved for economists.
For its part, the Senate has incorporated the creation of new figures in the financial sector, such as that of the Ombudsman, who will work on behalf of an enterprise, which will not require the authorization of the NCMV and will be able to provide its services for product marketing and attracting new customers to different investment firms at the same time.
