What insurance do I need?
Motor insurance, which covers the driver in the face of potential loss, implies an important expense that will depend on various factors, such as age, sex, seniority of driving licence, civil status, type of vehicle to be ensured or the actual use, among others.
Having a car is the main thing.
And it's that, choosing the right car insurance is even harder than choosing the vehicle model.
And that is, choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the vehicle model.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insurer.
This compromise is materialized by an insurance contract, which establishes that the company receives the value of the premium granted and in exchange it becomes responsible for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of a loss.
The premium is the price of insurance, which takes into account various factors, such as age, sex, seniority of driving licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be ensured or the actual use, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices on the basis of statistics, so that the higher the likelihood of an accident, the higher the rate to be paid.
For this reason, people over 25 years of age and women must pay lower premiums, as statistics show that they have a lower rate of claims than they are careful.
Similarly, using censuses, companies have concluded that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use of the vehicle will affect the frequency, and therefore the likelihood of an accident.
By increasing the frequency the probabilities increase.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when setting the premium price.
For this reason, the driver must carefully study the situation in order to choose the car insurance that best suits his profile.
We will present here the most significant variables when choosing one or the other type of insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insurer, offers it a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 must face various disadvantages when entering into an insurance contract at an affordable price, such as low driving experience and old driving licence.
Although the ideal to be well insured is insurance at any risk, other more economical options exist.
The most anticipated drivers can opt for insurance at any risk with freeness, so that they get coverage from insurance at any risk but at a more affordable price.
This form of agreement implies that the client pays part of the disaster.
"The part of the amount of the disaster the customer will pay will be established according to the value of the premium, which will be higher the amount will be lower," said Luis Noguera, the responsible in Spain of First Europe, online insurance mediator.
Another option is extended third-party insurance, so that the customer ensures protection to deal with damage caused to third-party customers, but for those caused on his own car.
In addition, it would be covered against theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
A tip.
If you're a 25-year-old, try to be cautious and avoid the damage as far as possible, since this will affect the bonus, which can reduce the future insurance price.
A bonus is a reduction in the basic rate that the company has.
On the contrary, a penalty is an increase in the basic tariff.
"Bonifications and sanctions will depend on the company and its profit.
If the company has had a good year it will be able to increase the bonus," explains Noguera.
Beyond the age of 25 this becomes easier for drivers when entering into a contract with insurance, as the rate of claims is reduced thanks to accumulated experience.
That is why it is better to choose insurance at all risk with freeness.
"Usually young people cannot take advantage of prior experience acquired after an accident," says the director of the European company in Spain and adds that the majority of accidents occur during the second year of driving, once the 'novice fear' has passed.
However, if the customer is married but has no children yet, it is preferable for him to negotiate insurance at any risk, as long as his economic situation allows him.
Marriages with children are considered by insurers as people with the lowest rate of death, because increases will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be insurance at any risk with freeness (may be EUR 300), or insurance to third parties extended from the third year of life of the vehicle when the insured person has a high level of bonus.
"They have a more relaxed drive and they have greater purchasing power to allow themselves the luxury to assume a greater amount of franchises," Justice Luis Noguera said.
For pensioners, insurance at all risk with free will is preferable (in the amount of EUR 150), or extended third party insurance when the insurer has a high level of bonus.
It must be said that motor insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver in the face of possible disasters, but also because it represents an important expense, that is why it is essential to properly study the insurance that most suits us according to our personal situation.
